law.text:
A federal association may convert to a Maryland savings and loan association if:
Its principal office is in this State;
Its members approve;
The Division Director approves; and
Immediately upon filing its articles of incorporation with the State Department of Assessments and Taxation, the association will convert to a commercial bank under the provisions of §§ 9-631 through 9-639 of this subtitle or convert to a federally chartered savings and loan association under §§ 9-613 through 9-615 of this subtitle.
